<p><b>Phillips Exeter Academy</b> (also called <b>Exeter</b>, <b>Phillips Exeter</b> or <b>PEA</b>) is a <a href="/wiki/Co-educational" title="Co-educational" class="mw-redirect">co-educational</a> independent <a href="/wiki/Boarding_school" title="Boarding school">boarding school</a> for grades 9–12 and postgraduates, located on 619&#160;acres (2.51&#160;km<sup>2</sup>) in <a href="/wiki/Exeter,_New_Hampshire" title="Exeter, New Hampshire">Exeter, New Hampshire</a>, <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">USA</a>, 50&#160;miles (80&#160;km) north of <a href="/wiki/Boston" title="Boston">Boston</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2" title=""><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup>.</p>
<p>Early alumni include US Senator <a href="/wiki/Daniel_Webster" title="Daniel Webster">Daniel Webster</a> (1796), US President <a href="/wiki/Franklin_Pierce" title="Franklin Pierce">Franklin Pierce</a> (1820), <a href="/wiki/Abraham_Lincoln" title="Abraham Lincoln">Abraham Lincoln</a>'s son <a href="/wiki/Robert_Lincoln" title="Robert Lincoln" class="mw-redirect">Robert Lincoln</a> (1860), <a href="/wiki/Ulysses_S._Grant,_Jr." title="Ulysses S. Grant, Jr.">Ulysses S. Grant, Jr.</a> (1870), "grandfather of football" <a href="/wiki/Amos_Alonzo_Stagg" title="Amos Alonzo Stagg">Amos Alonzo Stagg</a> (1880), and <a href="/wiki/Pulitzer_Prize" title="Pulitzer Prize">Pulitzer Prize</a>-winning author <a href="/wiki/Booth_Tarkington" title="Booth Tarkington">Booth Tarkington</a> (1889). Exeter students and alumni call themselves "Exonians”.</p>
<p>Exeter is noted for its <i>Harkness</i> education, a system based on a conference format of teacher and student interaction, similar to the <a href="/wiki/Socrates" title="Socrates">Socratic</a> method of learning through asking questions and creating discussions.<sup id="cite_ref-www_3-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-www-3" title=""><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>The school's traditional rival is <a href="/wiki/Phillips_Academy" title="Phillips Academy">Phillips Academy</a> (Andover), and the <a href="/wiki/Exeter-Andover_Rivalry" title="Exeter-Andover Rivalry">annual Exeter-Andover Football game</a> has been played since 1878.</p>
